Hey Nicole, during the clip when you baked with Sage in the carrier, my thoughts where: I'd wore her on my back.
I have three children (now 15, 13 and 9) and I really loved to wear them on my back as babies. For me that was way more comfortable than wearing them on the front, which I also did when they where really little. I am not sure if that will be possible with the carrier you have. I always used a wrap at first when they where little for wearing them on the front.
Later (about Sages age) I wore them on my back in an Ergo Baby Carrier or an Manduca Carrier. But I don't know if these are outdated now.
As soon as I had my second child (the first was 2,5 years at that point) I could not imagine how to survive without a carrier.
If you have baby on you back you have your hands and front free to do things with the toddler.
Also older babies often like it to be on the back because they can see more than on your front (if faced to you).
I always heard that facing baby outwards when carrying on your front is supposed to be bad for their hips (and gives a lot of pressure on babys private area, which is especially bad for boys). Love from Germany, Salo
